Today  Rwanda NGOs Forum  on HIV/AIDS and H.P Launches 
Youth Action Against Cervical Cancer alongside @urphsa is a nationwide call for young people to lead prevention, awareness, and early detection efforts in support of Rwanda Ministry of Health’s Mission 2027 elimination strategy.

Cervical cancer is preventable and treatable when detected early. Our message is clear: Test to Know, Act to Protect. HPV vaccination and regular screening save lives.

No woman or girl should be left behind because of stigma, misinformation, poverty, or vaccine hesitancy.

Let’s raise our voices, start conversations, and take action. Encourage a sister, friend, or mother to get screened and support HPV vaccination.

Together, we can prevent cervical cancer and build a healthier future for all.

#YouthAgainstCervicalCancerRw #TestToKnowRw #ScreeningSavesLivesRw
